    "In this project, this was facilitatedï¿½ for exaï¿½pleï¿½ by using standardized icons and tooltips that guided the children on how to begin to build a classifier.",
    "Moreoverï¿½ the tool divided the ML workflow into phases in order to decrease their cognitive load by structuring the process in ways that focused children's attention on the critical features of each (sub)task at hand.",
    "For exaï¿½pleï¿½ the built-in scaffolding of the tool restricted the options visible to the learner so that the learner could only proceed to the build behavior after finishing their planning and prototyping of the classifier.",
    "To ï¿½otivate the children to follow the workflow to the endï¿½ the tool also provided rooï¿½ for children to personalize their projects by iï¿½porting their own data (e.g.",
    "pho-tosï¿½ voicesï¿½ ï¿½usicï¿½ artworkï¿½ textï¿½ aniï¿½ationsï¿½ graphics)ï¿½ and thusï¿½ they had the agency to affect their own course of action as well as the behaviors of the designed classifier."
